  "details": "libproxy offers the following features:* extremely small core footprint (&lt; 35k).* no external dependencies within libproxy core.(libproxy plugins may have dependencies).* only 3 functions in the stable external API.* dynamic adjustment to changing network topology.* a standard way of dealing with proxy settings across all scenarios.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nurl::recvline in url.cpp in libproxy 0.4.x through 0.4.15 allows a remote HTTP server to trigger uncontrolled recursion via a response composed of an infinite stream that lacks a newline character. This leads to stack exhaustion.(CVE-2020-25219)",
